发信人: thousand (壹仟), 信区: Oversea<br />标  题: 纽约时报爆料牛校mm哄抢男生资源...zz<br />发信站: 水木社区 (Fri Feb 12 05:04:17 2010), 站内<br /><br />上周五《纽约时报》长文披露北卡mm争夺男生的惨烈场景，相当惊心动魄：<br /><br />北卡没有工科学院，加上mm们一般成绩较好，女生在数量上占优。报道称近60%的女生<br />让该校感觉像女子学校，而我觉得一般要能够得上和尚/尼姑学校称号，至少要7:3。我<br />质疑6:4的比率mm争抢壮汉的必要性。<br />"North Carolina, with a student body that is nearly 60 percent female, is<br />just one of many large universities that at times feel eerily like women’s<br />colleges."<br /><br /><br />来自北卡的Jayne Dallas同学替我解开问题答案：牛校的mm们一般都比较挑，先排除了<br />一半wsn，剩下看得上的，其中一半有主了，所以其实，猎物并不多。<br />“Out of that 40 percent, there are maybe 20 percent that we would consider,<br /> and out of those 20, 10 have girlfriends, so all the girls are fighting<br />over that other 10 percent,”<br /><br /><br />也难怪mm在这种环境下抱怨找不到男朋友，每逢周五晚上以泪洗面无处寻伴：<br />"But surrounded by so many other successful women, they often find it harder<br /> than expected to find a date on a Friday night."<br /><br /><br />Andrew同学披露这种压力有一些来自家长，称单身遭到家长鄙视：<br />“My parents think there is something wrong with me because I don’t have a<br />boyfriend, and I don’t hang out with a lot of guys,” said Ms. Andrew, who<br />had a large circle of male friends in high school. "<br /><br /><br />在这样供需极度不平衡的市场下，男生个个得意洋洋，炫耀轻松可以找到女朋友，随便<br />去酒吧溜达一圈，第二天就有mm短信无数：<br />Several male students acknowledged that the math skewed pleasantly in their<br />favor. “You don’t have to work that hard,” said Matt Garofalo, a senior<br />at North Carolina. “You meet a girl at a late-night restaurant, she’s<br />texting you the next day.”<br /><br /><br />Kelly Lynch的描述证实了竞争的惨烈：某个平静的夜晚，她正在酒吧和一个gg聊天，<br />突然天空猛降一只母鹰瞬时将猎物夺走，再抬头张望时，猎物已经被津津享用了——一<br />女生横势跳出，把她的gg拉走，然后在她面前和他跳开了舞。<br />"I was talking to a friend at a bar, and this girl just came up out of<br />nowhere, grabbed him by the wrist, spun him around and took him out to the<br />dance floor and started grinding"<br /><br /><br />Katie Deray对此很无奈，称女生太多，男生像熊瞎子掰玉米，边啃边扔：<br />"“If a guy is not getting what he wants, he can quickly and abruptly go to<br />"“If a guy is not getting what he wants, he can quickly and abruptly go to<br />the next one, because there are so many of us,” said Katie Deray"<br /><br /><br />甚至，更惨的是，在这种恶性竞争下，mm还得忍受wsn们的不忠，以换取稳定的关系—<br />—北卡的男生过着无数男人梦想的生活...<br />"As for a man’s cheating, “that’s a thing that girls let slide, because<br />you have to,” said Emily Kennard, a junior at North Carolina. “If you don<br />’t let it slide, you don’t have a boyfriend.”<br /><br /><br />详细原文请看：<br />http://www.nytimes.com/2010/02/07/fashion/07campus.html?ref=style<br /><br /><br /><br />在众狼磨爪霍霍扑向北卡前，特地从U.S.News的《2009 Ultimate College Guide》中<br />摘出美国女生比率最高的前20学校：<br /><br />Texas Woman’s University  93%<br />Nova Southeastern University (FL)  74%<br />Adelphi University (NY)  72%<br />New School (NY)  71%<br />Regent University (VA)  69%<br />Barry University (FL)  68%<br />University of Bridgeport (CT)  68%<br />University of North Carolina–Greensboro  68%<br />Loyola University Chicago  65%<br />University of La Verne (CA)  64%<br />University of San Francisco  63%<br />Union Institute and University (OH)  63%<br />Paci&#64257;c University (OR)  63%<br />Azusa Paci&#64257;c University (CA)  63%<br />University of Memphis  62%<br />New York University  62%<br />Texas A&M University–Commerce  62%<br />Georgia State University  61%<br />Biola University (CA)  61%<br />Pace University (NY)  60%<br /><br />http://blog.sina.com.cn/s/blog_64d644080100gr1s.html<br /><br /><br />--<br /><br />※ 来源:·水木社区 newsmth.net·[FROM: 211.99.222.*]